  "text": "Obtained gene copy numbers were corrected for inhibition by spiking environmental DNA extracts with standard DNA as described earlier [CITATION_1] . Obtained inhibition factors ranged from 0.2-1.0, 0.1-1.0, and 0.1-1.0 for narG, nosZ, and 16S rRNA genes, respectively. Copy numbers of narG, nosZ, and 16S rRNA genes were compared between treatments and time points by Tukey's HSD test in IBM SPSS 22 after testing for normal distribution in R.",
